<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="114" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,326,1686]" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,398,425]" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">Description</emphasis>
. Body markedly flattened. Carapace rounded, longer as wide, distinctly narrowing anteriorly (
<bibRefCitation author="Garth" box="[159,293,434,461]" firstAuthor="Garth" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" pagination="1 - 55" refId="ref21540" refString="Garth, J. S. (1958) Brachyura of the Pacific coast of America, Oxyrhyncha. Allan Hancock Pacific Expeditions, 21 (1 &amp; 2), i-xxii + 1 - 499 &amp; 501 - 854, pls. A-Z 4 + 1 - 55." type="book chapter" year="1958">Garth 1958</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 4, fig. 2). Carapace resting on setting gutter (
<bibRefCitation author="Drach &amp; Guinot" box="[857,1112,435,461]" firstAuthor="Drach" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" pagination="715 - 720" refId="ref20996" refString="Drach, P. &amp; Guinot, D. (1982) Connexions morphologiques et fonctionnelles d'un type nouveau dans le squelette des Brachyoures du genre Paradasygius [sic] Garth (carapace, pleurites, sternites, pleon). Comptes rendus hebdomadaires des Seances de l'Academie des Sciences, Serie 3, 295, 715 - 720." type="journal article" year="1982">Drach &amp; Guinot 1982</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 1, fig. 5). Carapace dorsal surface covered with fine granulations and some occasional larger ones, with shallow grooves (
<bibRefCitation author="Santana, W. R. A." box="[1274,1432,471,497]" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" refId="ref24839" refString="Santana, W. R. A. (2008) Revisao taxonomica e relacoes filogeneticas em Inachoididae Dana, 1851 (Crustacea, Brachyura, Majoidea). Unpublished doctoral thesis, Universidade de Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo, 244 pp." type="book" year="2008">Santana 2008</bibRefCitation>
: figs. 49A, 50A). Rostrum simple, short, as narrow triangle. Preorbital tooth absent. Postorbital tooth large, curving around eye, forming postocular cup (supraocular eave) accommodating eyestalk in resting position (
<bibRefCitation author="Santana, W. R. A." box="[1275,1432,543,569]" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" refId="ref24839" refString="Santana, W. R. A. (2008) Revisao taxonomica e relacoes filogeneticas em Inachoididae Dana, 1851 (Crustacea, Brachyura, Majoidea). Unpublished doctoral thesis, Universidade de Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo, 244 pp." type="book" year="2008">Santana 2008</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 49A, B). Eyes large, flattened. Antenna: basal article adjacent to urinary article, long: with two teeth on inner margin, outer angle conspicuously projecting dorsally by long, narrow tooth; antennal movable portion entirely visible in dorsal view at side of rostrum (
<bibRefCitation author="Santana, W. R. A." box="[616,774,651,677]" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" refId="ref24839" refString="Santana, W. R. A. (2008) Revisao taxonomica e relacoes filogeneticas em Inachoididae Dana, 1851 (Crustacea, Brachyura, Majoidea). Unpublished doctoral thesis, Universidade de Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo, 244 pp." type="book" year="2008">Santana 2008</bibRefCitation>
: figs. 49A, 50A). Proepistome laterally compressed, forming slightly recessed septum not joining rudimentary epistome. Branchiostegite very reduced; branchial chamber reduced to narrow space due to flattening of body, probably not functional posteriorly, without gills at level of last pereiopods. Mxp3: ischium narrow, crista dentata formed by triangular teeth; merus narrow at base, then strongly cordiform; coxa short, prolonged by distal lobe to embayment (
<bibRefCitation author="Rathbun" box="[852,1014,794,821]" firstAuthor="Rathbun" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" pagination="1 - 613" refId="ref24756" refString="Rathbun, M. J. (1925) The spider crabs of America. Bulletin of the U. S. National Museum, 129, 1 - 613. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.129. i" type="journal article" year="1925">Rathbun 1925</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 50, as 
<taxonomicName authority="Rathbun, 1897" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1897" baseAuthorityName="Bell" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[1139,1371,795,821]" class="Malacostraca" family="Inachoididae" genus="Dasygyius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depressus">
<emphasis box="[1139,1371,795,821]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">Dasygyius depressus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Guinot &amp; Richer de Forges" firstAuthor="Guinot" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" pagination="453 - 502" refId="ref22156" refString="Guinot, D. &amp; Richer de Forges, B. (1997) Affinites entre les Hymenosomatidae MacLeay, 1838 et les Inachoididae Dana, 1851 (Crustacea Decapoda Brachyura). Zoosystema, 19 (2 &amp; 3), 453 - 502." type="journal article" year="1997">Guinot &amp; Richer de Forges 1997</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 14A). Thoracic sternum flat, except the first three inflated sternites (
<bibRefCitation author="Santana, W. R. A." box="[1276,1432,831,857]" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" refId="ref24839" refString="Santana, W. R. A. (2008) Revisao taxonomica e relacoes filogeneticas em Inachoididae Dana, 1851 (Crustacea, Brachyura, Majoidea). Unpublished doctoral thesis, Universidade de Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo, 244 pp." type="book" year="2008">Santana 2008</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 49B; 
<bibRefCitation author="Guinot" box="[257,402,867,893]" firstAuthor="Guinot" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" pagination="22 - 40" refId="ref21874" refString="Guinot, D. (2012) Remarks on Inachoididae Dana, 1851, with the description of a new genus and the resurrection of Stenorhynchinae Dana, 1851, and recognition of the inachid subfamily Podochelinae Neumann, 1878 (Crustacea, Decapoda, Brachyura, Majoidea). Zootaxa, 3416 (1), 22 - 40. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3416.1.2" type="journal article" year="2012">Guinot 2012</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 3C; 
<bibRefCitation author="Guinot" box="[505,713,867,893]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Guinot" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" pagination="285 - 322" refId="ref22322" refString="Guinot, D., Carbot-Chanona, G. &amp; Vega, F. J. (2019) Archaeochiapasidae n. fam., a new early Cenomanian brachyuran family from Chiapas, Mexico, new insights on Lecythocaridae Schweitzer &amp; Feldmann, 2009, and phylogenetic implications (Crustacea, Decapoda, Brachyura, Eubrachyura). Geodiversitas, 41 (7), 285 - 322. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / geodiversitas 2019 v 41 a 7" type="journal article" year="2019">
Guinot 
<emphasis box="[590,646,867,893]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 16B). Absence of sternum/pterygostome junction, sternite 4 not laterally extended; suture 3/4 short, only lateral, forming deep pocket (
<bibRefCitation author="Guinot" box="[973,1119,903,929]" firstAuthor="Guinot" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" pagination="22 - 40" refId="ref21874" refString="Guinot, D. (2012) Remarks on Inachoididae Dana, 1851, with the description of a new genus and the resurrection of Stenorhynchinae Dana, 1851, and recognition of the inachid subfamily Podochelinae Neumann, 1878 (Crustacea, Decapoda, Brachyura, Majoidea). Zootaxa, 3416 (1), 22 - 40. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3416.1.2" type="journal article" year="2012">Guinot 2012</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 3C, D); Milne-Edwards openings not separated from chelipeds. Presence of very wide sternal extensions joining exposed pleurites (sternum/pleurites connections) between P1/P2, P2/P3, P3/P4, P4/P5. Pleurites regularly connecting medially and fused to carapace by pillars (
<bibRefCitation author="Drach &amp; Guinot" box="[404,654,1011,1037]" firstAuthor="Drach" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" pagination="715 - 720" refId="ref20996" refString="Drach, P. &amp; Guinot, D. (1982) Connexions morphologiques et fonctionnelles d'un type nouveau dans le squelette des Brachyoures du genre Paradasygius [sic] Garth (carapace, pleurites, sternites, pleon). Comptes rendus hebdomadaires des Seances de l'Academie des Sciences, Serie 3, 295, 715 - 720." type="journal article" year="1982">Drach &amp; Guinot 1982</bibRefCitation>
). Pleurites 5–8 exposed, rather wide, each sclerite pointed at each end and covered with small granules (
<bibRefCitation author="Drach &amp; Guinot" box="[535,790,1047,1073]" firstAuthor="Drach" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" pagination="715 - 720" refId="ref20996" refString="Drach, P. &amp; Guinot, D. (1982) Connexions morphologiques et fonctionnelles d'un type nouveau dans le squelette des Brachyoures du genre Paradasygius [sic] Garth (carapace, pleurites, sternites, pleon). Comptes rendus hebdomadaires des Seances de l'Academie des Sciences, Serie 3, 295, 715 - 720." type="journal article" year="1982">Drach &amp; Guinot 1982</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 1, fig. 5; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hendrickx" box="[946,1132,1047,1073]" firstAuthor="Hendrickx" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" refId="ref22525" refString="Hendrickx, M. E. (1999) Los Cangrejos Braquiuros (Crustacea: Brachyura: Majoidea y Parthenopoidea) del Pacifico Mexicano. Comision Nacional para el Conocimiento y Uso de la Biodiversidad (CONABIO) e Instituto de Ciencias del Mar y Limnologia, UNAM, Mexico City, 274 pp., 13 pls." type="book" year="1999">Hendrickx 1999</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 2A, B; 
<bibRefCitation author="Santana, W. R. A." box="[1275,1432,1047,1073]" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" refId="ref24839" refString="Santana, W. R. A. (2008) Revisao taxonomica e relacoes filogeneticas em Inachoididae Dana, 1851 (Crustacea, Brachyura, Majoidea). Unpublished doctoral thesis, Universidade de Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo, 244 pp." type="book" year="2008">Santana 2008</bibRefCitation>
: figs. 49A, 50A). Male chelipeds stout; palm inflated, subglobular; fingers narrowly gaping at base, crenulate on prehensile margins (
<bibRefCitation author="Rathbun" box="[378,542,1118,1145]" firstAuthor="Rathbun" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" pagination="1 - 613" refId="ref24756" refString="Rathbun, M. J. (1925) The spider crabs of America. Bulletin of the U. S. National Museum, 129, 1 - 613. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.129. i" type="journal article" year="1925">Rathbun 1925</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 51, as 
<taxonomicName authority="Rathbun, 1897" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1897" baseAuthorityName="Bell" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[672,905,1119,1145]" class="Malacostraca" family="Inachoididae" genus="Dasygyius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depressus">
<emphasis box="[672,905,1119,1145]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">Dasygyius depressus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Garth" box="[920,1051,1118,1145]" firstAuthor="Garth" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" pagination="1 - 55" refId="ref21540" refString="Garth, J. S. (1958) Brachyura of the Pacific coast of America, Oxyrhyncha. Allan Hancock Pacific Expeditions, 21 (1 &amp; 2), i-xxii + 1 - 499 &amp; 501 - 854, pls. A-Z 4 + 1 - 55." type="book chapter" year="1958">Garth 1958</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 4, fig. 2; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hendrickx" box="[1201,1387,1119,1145]" firstAuthor="Hendrickx" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" refId="ref22525" refString="Hendrickx, M. E. (1999) Los Cangrejos Braquiuros (Crustacea: Brachyura: Majoidea y Parthenopoidea) del Pacifico Mexicano. Comision Nacional para el Conocimiento y Uso de la Biodiversidad (CONABIO) e Instituto de Ciencias del Mar y Limnologia, UNAM, Mexico City, 274 pp., 13 pls." type="book" year="1999">Hendrickx 1999</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 40B). Female chelipeds weaker than legs, palm not swollen (
<bibRefCitation author="Rathbun" box="[827,990,1154,1181]" firstAuthor="Rathbun" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" pagination="1 - 613" refId="ref24756" refString="Rathbun, M. J. (1925) The spider crabs of America. Bulletin of the U. S. National Museum, 129, 1 - 613. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.129. i" type="journal article" year="1925">Rathbun 1925</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 274, figs. 7–8, as 
<taxonomicName authority="Rathbun, 1897" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1897" baseAuthorityName="Bell" baseAuthorityYear="1835" class="Malacostraca" family="Inachoididae" genus="Dasygyius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depressus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">Dasygyius depressus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Ambulatory legs very long, granulate and hairy (
<bibRefCitation author="Hendrickx" box="[766,954,1191,1217]" firstAuthor="Hendrickx" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" refId="ref22525" refString="Hendrickx, M. E. (1999) Los Cangrejos Braquiuros (Crustacea: Brachyura: Majoidea y Parthenopoidea) del Pacifico Mexicano. Comision Nacional para el Conocimiento y Uso de la Biodiversidad (CONABIO) e Instituto de Ciencias del Mar y Limnologia, UNAM, Mexico City, 274 pp., 13 pls." type="book" year="1999">Hendrickx 1999</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 40A; 
<bibRefCitation author="Santana, W. R. A." box="[1077,1234,1191,1217]" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" refId="ref24839" refString="Santana, W. R. A. (2008) Revisao taxonomica e relacoes filogeneticas em Inachoididae Dana, 1851 (Crustacea, Brachyura, Majoidea). Unpublished doctoral thesis, Universidade de Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo, 244 pp." type="book" year="2008">Santana 2008</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 47B). Pleon: first somite dorsal, granular, produced into long, conical, acute spine in both sexes (
<bibRefCitation author="Drach &amp; Guinot" box="[1077,1326,1227,1253]" firstAuthor="Drach" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" pagination="715 - 720" refId="ref20996" refString="Drach, P. &amp; Guinot, D. (1982) Connexions morphologiques et fonctionnelles d'un type nouveau dans le squelette des Brachyoures du genre Paradasygius [sic] Garth (carapace, pleurites, sternites, pleon). Comptes rendus hebdomadaires des Seances de l'Academie des Sciences, Serie 3, 295, 715 - 720." type="journal article" year="1982">Drach &amp; Guinot 1982</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 1, fig. 4; 
<bibRefCitation author="Santana, W. R. A." box="[181,337,1263,1289]" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" refId="ref24839" refString="Santana, W. R. A. (2008) Revisao taxonomica e relacoes filogeneticas em Inachoididae Dana, 1851 (Crustacea, Brachyura, Majoidea). Unpublished doctoral thesis, Universidade de Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo, 244 pp." type="book" year="2008">Santana 2008</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 50B). Male pleon with somites 1-5 free, somites 6 being fused to telson (pleotelson); female pleon (
<bibRefCitation author="Rathbun" box="[230,395,1298,1325]" firstAuthor="Rathbun" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" pagination="1 - 613" refId="ref24756" refString="Rathbun, M. J. (1925) The spider crabs of America. Bulletin of the U. S. National Museum, 129, 1 - 613. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.129. i" type="journal article" year="1925">Rathbun 1925</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 274, fig. 5, as 
<taxonomicName authority="Rathbun, 1897" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1897" baseAuthorityName="Bell" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[612,846,1299,1325]" class="Malacostraca" family="Inachoididae" genus="Dasygyius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depressus">
<emphasis box="[612,846,1299,1325]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">Dasygyius depressus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) with somites 1–4 free, somites 5, 6 being fused to telson (pleotelson). Male gonopore partially condylar, partially coxal (
<bibRefCitation author="Guinot" box="[931,1194,1335,1362]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Guinot" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" pagination="1 - 414" refId="ref22407" refString="Guinot, D., Tavares, M. &amp; Castro, P. (2013) Significance of the sexual openings and supplementary structures on the phylogeny of brachyuran crabs (Crustacea, Decapoda, Brachyura), with new nomina for higher-ranked podotreme taxa. Zootaxa, 3665 (1), 1 - 414. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3665.1.1" type="journal article" year="2013">
Guinot 
<emphasis box="[1017,1065,1335,1361]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">et al</emphasis>
. 2013: 127
</bibRefCitation>
). G1 straight, without developed lobe, aperture subapical (
<bibRefCitation author="Garth" box="[557,690,1370,1397]" firstAuthor="Garth" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" pagination="1 - 55" refId="ref21540" refString="Garth, J. S. (1958) Brachyura of the Pacific coast of America, Oxyrhyncha. Allan Hancock Pacific Expeditions, 21 (1 &amp; 2), i-xxii + 1 - 499 &amp; 501 - 854, pls. A-Z 4 + 1 - 55." type="book chapter" year="1958">Garth 1958</bibRefCitation>
: pl. E, fig. 5). Vulvae located on anteriorly displaced sternite 6, as expansions projecting on sternites 5 and even 4. Pleonal-locking mechanism: marked, often pointed button on sternite 5, near suture 5/6; socket on pleotelson (
<bibRefCitation author="Guinot &amp; Richer de Forges" box="[652,1026,1443,1470]" firstAuthor="Guinot" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" pagination="453 - 502" refId="ref22156" refString="Guinot, D. &amp; Richer de Forges, B. (1997) Affinites entre les Hymenosomatidae MacLeay, 1838 et les Inachoididae Dana, 1851 (Crustacea Decapoda Brachyura). Zoosystema, 19 (2 &amp; 3), 453 - 502." type="journal article" year="1997">Guinot &amp; Richer de Forges 1997</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 14B, C).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="114" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,326,1686]" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1479,1505]" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">Remarks</emphasis>
. Based on the analysis of larval characters, 
<bibRefCitation author="Marques &amp; Pohle" box="[802,1081,1479,1506]" firstAuthor="Marques" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" pagination="241 - 262" refId="ref23331" refString="Marques, F. P. L. &amp; Pohle, G. (1998) The use of structural reduction in phylogenetic reconstruction of decapods and a phylogenetic hypothesis for fifteen genera of Majidae: testing previous hypotheses and assumptions. Invertebrate Reproduction and Development, 33 (2 - 3), 241 - 262. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 07924259.1998.9652636" type="journal article" year="1998">
<collectingRegion box="[802,900,1480,1506]" country="Italy" name="Marche" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">Marques</collectingRegion>
&amp; Pohle (1998)
</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Garth" authorityYear="1958" box="[1217,1383,1479,1505]" class="Malacostraca" family="Inachoididae" genus="Paradasygyius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1217,1383,1479,1505]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">Paradasygyius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authority="Rathbun, 1897" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1897" baseAuthorityName="Bell" baseAuthorityYear="1835" class="Malacostraca" family="Inachoididae" genus="Dasygyius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depressus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">depressus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) an inachine, as the sister taxon of 
<taxonomicName authority="Weber, 1795" authorityName="Weber" authorityYear="1795" box="[626,865,1514,1541]" class="Malacostraca" family="Inachidae" genus="Inachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[626,715,1515,1541]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">Inachus</emphasis>
Weber, 1795
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pohle &amp; Marques" box="[876,1154,1515,1542]" firstAuthor="Pohle" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" pagination="739 - 760" refId="ref24476" refString="Pohle, G. &amp; Marques, F. (2000) Larval stages of Paradasygyius depressus (Bell, 1835) (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Majoidea) and a phylogenetic analysis for 21 genera of Majidae. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 113 (3), 739 - 760." type="journal article" year="2000">
Pohle &amp; 
<collectingRegion box="[974,1072,1516,1542]" country="Italy" name="Marche" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">Marques</collectingRegion>
(2000)
</bibRefCitation>
found no larval evidence to support the monophyly of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1851" box="[482,630,1551,1577]" class="Malacostraca" family="Inachidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Inachoidinae">Inachoidinae</taxonomicName>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Marques &amp; Pohle" box="[690,1016,1551,1578]" firstAuthor="Marques" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" pagination="71 - 82" refId="ref23399" refString="Marques, F. P. L. &amp; Pohle, G. (2003) Searching for larval support for majid subfamilies (Crustacea: Brachyura) with particular reference to Inachoidinae Dana, 1851. Invertebrate Reproduction and Development, 43, 71 - 82. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 07924259.2003.9652523" type="journal article" year="2003">
<collectingRegion box="[690,788,1552,1578]" country="Italy" name="Marche" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">Marques</collectingRegion>
&amp; Pohle (2003: 77)
</bibRefCitation>
were unable to provide a single synapomorphy for the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Drach &amp; Guinot" authorityYear="1983" box="[363,511,1587,1613]" class="Malacostraca" family="Inachoididae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Inachoididae</taxonomicName>
, “with the clade (
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1880" box="[703,812,1588,1614]" class="Malacostraca" family="Inachoididae" genus="Anasimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[703,812,1588,1614]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">Anasimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Garth" authorityYear="1958" box="[827,993,1587,1613]" class="Malacostraca" family="Inachoididae" genus="Paradasygyius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[827,993,1587,1613]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">Paradasygyius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1860" box="[1009,1109,1587,1613]" class="Malacostraca" family="Inachoididae" genus="Collodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1009,1109,1587,1613]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">Collodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1871" box="[1136,1245,1588,1613]" class="Malacostraca" family="Inachoididae" genus="Pyromaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1136,1245,1588,1613]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">Pyromaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
)))” supported by some larval characters. See above 
<emphasis box="[537,811,1623,1649]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">
The family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Drach &amp; Guinot" authorityYear="1983" box="[663,811,1623,1649]" class="Malacostraca" family="Inachoididae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Inachoididae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,326,1686]" box="[199,550,1658,1686]" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,468,1658,1685]" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">Other included genera</emphasis>
. None.
</paragraph>
